Commented on #2266 Self-signing HTTPS certificate guide/documentation

Got it working without a reverse proxy How to Setup Encryption without reverse proxy I followed this guide on how to create own Certificate Authority Then installed the certificates on my raspberry pi where AdGuard Home is installed. Instructions are here After running sudo update-ca-certificates restart your AdGuardHome service ( systemctl restart AdGuardHome ) Now copy your-domainname.crt and yourdomainname.key to e.g. /opt/AdGuardHome/ Installing the certificates on AdGuardHome Login on the Web Panel Go to Settings Encryption Settings Enable Encryption Change Server Name to your-domainname Change other settings however you want / you probably want to enable https redirect to always use https Now set the "Certificate Path" to e.g. /opt/AdGuardHome/your-domainname.crt And change the "Private key path" to e.g. /opt/AdGuardHome/your-domainname.key Last but not least click Save Configuration
As you can see your certificate is NOT invalid and will be trusted by AdGuardHome! Now you can access your adguard home via https with https://your-domainname:YOUR-HTTPS-PORT without a reverse proxy
